APIOptions.description: Configuration options for the PrimeReact components.

props.name: appendTo
props.description: This option allows components with overlays like dropdowns or popups to be mounted into either the component or any DOM element, such as document body and self.

props.name: styleContainer
props.description: This option allows  `useStyle`  to insert dynamic CSS styles into a specific container. This is useful when styles need to be scoped such as in a Shadow DOM.

props.name: autoZIndex
props.description: ZIndexes are managed automatically to make sure layering of overlay components work seamlessly when combining multiple components. When autoZIndex is false, each group increments its zIndex within itself.

props.name: cssTransition
props.description: PrimeReact components utilize "react-transition-group" internally to implement animations. Setting "cssTransition" to "false" disables all animations.

props.name: filterMatchModeOptions
props.description: Default filter modes to display on DataTable filter menus.

props.name: hideOverlaysOnDocumentScrolling
props.description: Define behavior if the browser window is scrolled while displaying an overlay panel like a Dropdown or Calendar. Depending on your organization's accessibility needs some prefer panels to be closed on scrolling and some prefer the overlay follow the scroll.

props.name: inputStyle
props.description: Input fields have two styles: default (outlined with borders) and filled (background-colored). Applying 'p-input-filled' to an input's ancestor enables the filled style.

props.name: locale
props.description: The locale configuration sets up the language and region specific preferences.

props.name: nonce
props.description: The nonce value to use on dynamically generated style elements.

props.name: nullSortOrder
props.description: Determines how null values are sorted.

props.name: ripple
props.description: Ripple is an optional animation for the supported components such as buttons.

props.name: zIndex
props.description: ZIndexes are managed automatically to make sure layering of overlay components work seamlessly when combining multiple components. When autoZIndex is false, each group increments its zIndex within itself. Each property is optional, so when autoZIndex is enabled you can set the z-index for any component type, and the rest will be calculated automatically.

[Live Demo](https://www.primereact.org/autocomplete/)

values.name: appendTo
values.description: DOM element instance where the overlay panel should be mounted. Valid values are any DOM Element and "self". The "self" value is used to render a component where it is located.

values.description: When present, it specifies that the component should automatically get focus on load.

values.description: Focus the input field when the dropdown button is clicked if enabled.

values.name: dropdownIcon
values.description: Icon of the dropdown.

values.name: dropdownMode
values.description: Specifies the behavior dropdown button. Default "blank" mode sends an empty string and "current" mode sends the input value.

values.name: emptyMessage
values.description: Text to display when there is no data. Defaults to global value in i18n translation configuration.

values.description: Field of a suggested object to resolve and display.

values.name: forceSelection
values.description: When present, autocomplete clears the manual input if it does not match of the suggestions to force only accepting values from the suggestions.

props.name: id
props.description: Unique identifier of the element.

props.name: value
props.description: An array of objects to display.

props.description: Whether to show it even there is only one page.

props.description: The breakpoint to define the maximum width boundary when using stack responsive layout.

props.name: checkIcon
props.description: Icon to display in the checkbox.

props.description: Style class of the component.

props.description: Icon of the row toggler to display the row as collapsed.

props.name: columnResizeMode
props.description: Used to define the resize mode of the columns, valid values are "fit" and "expand".

props.name: compareSelectionBy
props.description: Algorithm to define if a row is selected, valid values are "equals" that compares by reference and "deepEquals" that compares all fields.

props.name: contextMenuSelection
props.description: Selected row in single mode or an array of values in multiple mode.

props.name: csvSeparator
props.description: Character to use as the csv separator.

props.name: currentPageReportTemplate
props.description: Template of the current page report element. Available placeholders are {currentPage}, {totalPages}, {rows}, {first}, {last} and {totalRecords}

props.name: dataKey
props.description: Name of the field that uniquely identifies a record in the data. Should be a unique business key to prevent re-rendering.

props.name: defaultSortOrder
props.description: Default sort order of an unsorted column.

props.name: dragSelection
props.description: When enabled, a rectangle that can be dragged can be used to make a range selection.

props.name: editMode
props.description: Defines editing mode, options are "cell" and "row".

props.name: editingRows
props.description: A collection of rows to represent the current editing data in row edit mode.

props.name: emptyMessage
props.description: Text to display when there is no data.

props.name: expandableRowGroups
props.description: Makes row groups toggleable, default is false.

props.name: expandedRowIcon
props.description: Icon of the row toggler to display the row as expanded.

props.name: expandedRows
props.description: A collection of rows or a map object row data keys that are expanded.

props.name: exportFilename
props.description: Name of the exported file.

props.name: filterDelay
props.description: Delay in milliseconds before filtering the data.

props.name: filterDisplay
props.description: Layout of the filter elements, valid values are "row" and "menu".

props.name: filterLocale
props.description: Locale to use in filtering. The default locale is the host environment's current locale.

props.name: filterIcon
props.description: Icon to display the current filtering status.

props.name: filterClearIcon
props.description: Icon to display when the filter can be cleared.

props.name: filters
props.description: An array of FilterMetadata objects to provide external filters.

props.name: first
props.description: Index of the first row to be displayed.

props.name: footer
props.description: Custom footer content of the table.

props.name: footerColumnGroup
props.description: ColumnGroup component for footer.

props.name: frozenValue
props.description: Items of the frozen part in scrollable DataTable.

props.name: frozenWidth
props.description: Width of the frozen part in scrollable DataTable.

props.name: frozenRow
props.description: Whether the row is frozen or not. Read-Only necessary for unstyled TypeScript definition.

props.name: globalFilter
props.description: Value of the global filter to use in filtering.

props.name: globalFilterFields
props.description: Define fields to be filtered globally.

props.name: globalFilterMatchMode
props.description: Defines filterMatchMode; "startsWith", "contains", "endsWith", "equals", "notEquals", "in", "lt", "lte", "gt", "gte" and "custom".

props.name: groupRowsBy
props.description: Used for either be grouped by a separate grouping row or using rowspan.

props.name: header
props.description: Custom header content of the table.

props.name: headerColumnGroup
props.description: ColumnGroup component for header.

props.name: lazy
props.description: Defines if data is loaded and interacted with in lazy manner.

props.name: loading
props.description: Displays a loader to indicate data load is in progress.

props.name: loadingIcon
props.description: The icon to show while indicating data load is in progress.

props.name: metaKeySelection
props.description: Defines whether metaKey is requred or not for the selection. When true metaKey needs to be pressed to select or unselect an item and when set to false selection of each item can be toggled individually. On touch enabled devices, metaKeySelection is turned off automatically.

props.name: multiSortMeta
props.description: An array of SortMeta objects to sort the data by default in multiple sort mode.

props.name: pageLinkSize
props.description: Number of page links to display.

props.name: paginator
props.description: When specified as true, enables the pagination.

props.name: paginatorClassName
props.description: Style class of the paginator element.

props.name: paginatorDropdownAppendTo

props.name: paginatorLeft
props.description: Content for the left side of the paginator.

props.name: paginatorPosition
props.description: Position of the paginator, options are "top","bottom" or "both".

props.name: paginatorRight
props.description: Content for the right side of the paginator.

props.name: paginatorTemplate
props.description: Template of the paginator. For details, refer to the template section of the paginator documentation for further options.

props.name: removableSort
props.description: When enabled, columns can have an un-sorted state.

props.name: reorderableColumns
props.description: When enabled, columns can be reordered using drag and drop.

props.name: reorderableRows
props.description: When enabled, rows can be reordered using drag and drop.

props.description: Defines the reorder indicator down icon.

props.description: Icon to display in the row editor init button.

props.name: rowEditorSaveIcon
props.description: Icon to display in the row editor save button.

props.name: rowGroupHeaderTemplate
props.description: Function to provide the content of row group header.

props.name: rowGroupMode
props.description: Defines the row grouping mode, valid values are "subheader" and "rowgroup".

props.name: rowHover
props.description: When enabled, background of the rows change on hover.

props.name: rows
props.description: Number of rows to display per page.

props.name: rowsPerPageOptions
props.description: Array of integer values to display inside rows per page dropdown.

props.name: scrollHeight
props.description: Height of the scroll viewport.

props.name: scrollable
props.description: When specified, enables horizontal and/or vertical scrolling.

props.name: selectAll
props.description: When specified, selects all rows on page.

props.name: selectOnEdit
props.description: Determines whether the cell editor will be opened when clicking to select any row on Selection and Cell Edit modes.

props.name: selectionAutoFocus
props.description: When a selectable row is clicked on RadioButton and Checkbox selection, it automatically decides whether to focus on elements such as checkbox or radio.

props.name: selectionAriaLabel
props.description: A field property from the row to add Select {field} and Unselect {field} ARIA labels to checkbox/radio buttons.

props.name: selectionPageOnly
props.description: When enabled with paginator and checkbox selection mode, the select all checkbox in the header will select all rows on the current page.

props.name: showGridlines
props.description: Whether to show grid lines between cells.

props.name: showHeaders
props.description: Whether to show headers.

props.name: showSelectAll
props.description: Whether to show the select all checkbox inside the datatable's header.

props.name: size
props.description: Define to set alternative sizes. Valid values: "small", "normal" and "large".

props.name: sortField
props.description: Property of a row data used for sorting, defaults to field.

props.name: sortMode
props.description: Defines whether sorting works on single column or on multiple columns.

props.name: sortIcon
props.description: Icon to display the current sorting status.

props.name: sortOrder
props.description: Order to sort the data by default.

props.name: stateKey
props.description: Unique identifier of a stateful table to use in state storage.

props.name: stateStorage
props.description: Defines where a stateful table keeps its state, valid values are "session" for sessionStorage, "local" for localStorage and "custom".

props.name: stripedRows
props.description: Whether to displays rows with alternating colors.

props.name: style
props.description: Inline style of the component.

props.name: tabIndex
props.description: Index of the element in tabbing order.

props.name: tableClassName
props.description: Style class of the table element.

props.name: tableStyle
props.description: Inline style of the table element.

props.name: totalRecords
props.description: Number of total records, defaults to length of value when not defined.

props.name: virtualScrollerOptions
props.description:
Whether to use the virtualScroller feature. The properties of VirtualScroller component can be used like an object in it.

Note: Currently only vertical orientation mode is supported.

props.description: Used to get the child elements of the component.

props.description: Uses to pass attributes to DOM elements inside the component.

props.description: Used to configure passthrough(pt) options of the component.

props.description: When enabled, it removes component related styles in the core.

props.description: Content to be displayed in tooltip.

props.description: When present, it specifies that the tooltip should be hidden.

props.description: Style class of the tooltip.

props.description: Position of the tooltip.

props.description: Event to show the tooltip if the event property is empty.

props.name: data-pr-hideevent
props.description: Event to hide the tooltip if the event property is empty.

props.description: Whether the tooltip will follow the mouse.

props.description: Defines top position of the tooltip in relation to the mouse when the mouseTrack is enabled.

props.name: data-pr-mousetrackleft
props.description: Defines left position of the tooltip in relation to the mouse when the mouseTrack is enabled.

props.name: data-pr-updatedelay
props.description: Delay to update the tooltip in milliseconds.

props.description: Delay to hide the tooltip in milliseconds.

props.description: Whether to hide tooltip when hovering over tooltip content.

props.name: data-pr-showondisabled
props.description: Whether to show tooltip for disabled elements.

values.name: currency
values.description:
The currency to use in currency formatting. Possible values are the [ISO 4217 currency codes](https://www.six-group.com/en/products-services/financial-information/data-standards.html#scrollTo=maintenance-agency), such as "USD" for the US dollar, "EUR" for the euro, or "CNY" for the Chinese RMB.
There is no default value; if the style is "currency", the currency property must be provided.

values.name: currencyDisplay
values.description: How to display the currency in currency formatting. Possible values are "symbol" to use a localized currency symbol such as , "code" to use the ISO currency code, "name" to use a localized currency name such as "dollar"; the default is "symbol".

values.name: maxFractionDigits
values.description:
The maximum number of fraction digits to use. Possible values are from 0 to 20; the default for plain number formatting is the larger of minimumFractionDigits and 3;
the default for currency formatting is the larger of minimumFractionDigits and the number of minor unit digits provided by the [ISO 4217 currency code list](https://www.six-group.com/en/products-services/financial-information/data-standards.html#scrollTo=maintenance-agency) (2 if the list doesn't provide that information).

the default for currency formatting is the number of minor unit digits provided by the [ISO 4217 currency code list](https://www.six-group.com/en/products-services/financial-information/data-standards.html#scrollTo=maintenance-agency) (2 if the list doesn't provide that information).
